    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for `Bun.INI`:\n\n## What needs to change (6 files)\n\n### 1. **CREATE** `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig` *(new file — the core work)*\nModeled after `JSON5Object.zig`. **Fully self-contained** — no dependency on `src/ini.zig` (that parser is npm-specific: requires a `DotEnv.Loader`, performs env-var expansion, supports `key[]` array syntax, etc.).\n\n- **`create()`** — returns a plain JS object with 2 methods\n- **`parse(input: string)`** — line-by-line INI parser:\n  - Skips blank lines and `;`/`#` full-line comments\n  - `[section]` creates a new nested object on `root`, becomes the active `current` object\n  - `key = value` sets a property on `current`\n  - Strips inline comments (` ;` / ` #` outside quotes)\n  - Type coerces: `true`/`false` → boolean, numeric strings → number, `\"quoted\"` → unquoted string, else raw string\n- **`stringify(obj)`** — two-pass serializer:\n  - Pass 1: root-level primitives → `key = value`\n  - Pass 2: root-level objects → `\\n[section]\\nkey = value`\n  - Uses `jsc.JSPropertyIterator` and `wtf.StringBuilder` (same as `JSON5Object.zig`)\n\n### 2. **MODIFY** `src/bun.js/api.zig` (line 34)\n```zig\npub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");\n```\n\n### 3. **MODIFY** `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` (3 spots)\n- Lazy callback constant (line ~70): `pub const INI = toJSLazyPropertyCallback(Bun.getINIObject);`\n- Getter function (line ~1289): `pub fn getINIObject(...) { return INIObject.create(globalThis); }`\n- Import alias (line ~2083): `const INIObject = bun.api.INIObject;`\n\n### 4. **MODIFY** `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` (1 line in hash table, after line 968)\n```\nINI    BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI    DontDelete|PropertyCallback\n```\n\n### 5. **MODIFY** `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`\nAdd `namespace INI { parse(input: string): object; stringify(input: object): string; }` with JSDoc.\n\n### 6. **CREATE** `test/js/bun/ini/bun-ini.test.ts`\nTests existence, parse (sections, comments, type coercion, inline comments), stringify (primitives, sections), and round-trip.",
